  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated WASH and Protection support for the most vulnerable in NWS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">World Vision (WV), together with Syria Relief (SR) propose a multi-sector intervention, in response to the WASH and protection needs of IDPs in Idlib Governorate. The proposed intervention is directly linked to the SCHF allocation strategy paper&#x2019;s objectives to upgrade IDP sites to ensure safe and dignified living conditions for the most vulnerable and to provide life-saving humanitarian assistance and protection to the most vulnerable.
In this project, World Vision Australia, World Vision New Zealand amp World Vision Switzerland are joint Partners with WV Syria and shall be jointly and severally responsible for the implementation of the Project.</narrative>
  </description>
